that brooding veneer

1010
00:40:08,155 --> 00:40:09,824
is part of your appeal
but I thought

1011
00:40:09,857 --> 00:40:11,291
I'd broken
through most of it.

1012
00:40:16,831 --> 00:40:18,098
I'm supposed to be
at Carla's Restaurant

1013
00:40:18,132 --> 00:40:20,567
celebrating
my son's baptism.

1014
00:40:20,600 --> 00:40:22,302
I see.

1015
00:40:22,336 --> 00:40:23,904
And you're here because?

1016
00:40:23,938 --> 00:40:25,940
Ah..

1017
00:40:25,973 --> 00:40:27,942
I don't want to feel
like an intruder, you know?

1018
00:40:27,975 --> 00:40:31,578
Like I have to share my son
with Carla's boyfriend.

1019
00:40:31,611 --> 00:40:34,048
Do you?

1020
00:40:34,081 --> 00:40:35,716
I mean, he gets to spend
all the time with him.

1021
00:40:35,750 --> 00:40:38,585
You know, how do I
compete with that?

1022
00:40:38,619 --> 00:40:40,087
You're his father, Peter.

1023
00:40:40,120 --> 00:40:42,890
You don't have to compete.

1024
00:40:42,923 --> 00:40:44,191
Then I thought
I'd come and see you

1025
00:40:44,224 --> 00:40:47,227
but, you know, you had
that lunch thing, so..

1026
00:40:47,261 --> 00:40:50,030
Are you jealous?

1027
00:40:50,064 --> 00:40:54,101
Well, you know, your
instincts were right.

1028
00:40:54,134 --> 00:40:56,804
Romano propositioned me.

1029
00:40:56,837 --> 00:40:59,006
Are you serious?
What'd you say?

1030
00:40:59,039 --> 00:41:01,642
I lied.
Said I don't date colleagues.

1031
00:41:01,676 --> 00:41:04,178
It's cowardly of me, I know.

1032
00:41:04,211 --> 00:41:06,313
Oh, that's okay.
I lied today, too.

1033
00:41:06,346 --> 00:41:08,215
‐ What, about me?
‐ Mm‐hmm.

1034
00:41:08,248 --> 00:41:11,819
So much for a relationship
without complications.

1035
00:41:16,190 --> 00:41:18,659
You know what?
Screw it.

1036
00:41:18,693 --> 00:41:20,795
‐ Come on. Let's go.
‐ Where?

1037
00:41:20,828 --> 00:41:22,830
To the party.
There's still time.

1038
00:41:22,863 --> 00:41:24,732
Peter, you don't have
to prove anything to me.

1039
00:41:24,765 --> 00:41:27,267
Elizabeth, I know that.
Look, I just want to go, okay.

1040
00:41:27,301 --> 00:41:28,769
Well, then you should go.

1041
00:41:28,803 --> 00:41:30,237
You should go alone
for your son.

1042
00:41:30,270 --> 00:41:31,605
This is his day.

1043
00:41:34,108 --> 00:41:35,643
Ah, yeah, you're right.

1044
00:41:37,745 --> 00:41:38,879
Hey, thanks.

1045
00:41:41,949 --> 00:41:45,352
Listen, um, if
it's not too late..

1046
00:41:45,385 --> 00:41:46,420
Hey, listen, I'll be up.

1047
00:41:46,453 --> 00:41:48,022
‐ Are you kidding?
‐ Oh.

1048
00:41:53,894 --> 00:41:55,295
Hey! Anna!

1049
00:41:55,329 --> 00:41:56,764
Hi, Carter.

1050
00:41:56,797 --> 00:41:58,365
‐ Want some cookie?
‐ Yeah.

1051
00:41:58,398 --> 00:42:00,367
‐ You off?
‐ Yep. You?

1052
00:42:00,400 --> 00:42:01,969
‐ Another six hours.
‐ Bummer.

1053
00:42:02,002 --> 00:42:03,437
Did you discharge
Mr. Lorenzo?

1054
00:42:03,470 --> 00:42:05,139
Yes. He even gave me his web
site address.

1055
00:42:05,172 --> 00:42:06,406
‐ Thank you very much
‐ Why?

1056
00:42:06,440 --> 00:42:08,108
So you could
feel like an idiot?

1057
00:42:11,779 --> 00:42:12,913
Max!
Hold on.

1058
00:42:37,938 --> 00:42:39,707
'Oh, sorry.'

1059
00:42:40,908 --> 00:42:42,176
That's okay.

1060
00:42:42,209 --> 00:42:44,945
‐ What time is it?
‐ Uh, 10:00 to 2:00.

1061
00:42:44,979 --> 00:42:47,314
‐ You on call?
‐ Um, I'm waiting for Carol.

1062
00:42:47,347 --> 00:42:50,751
She should be ready. T‐they
called it about a half hour ago.

1063
00:42:50,785 --> 00:42:52,152
Thanks.

1064
00:43:03,530 --> 00:43:05,465
‐ Hey.
‐ Hey.

1065
00:43:05,499 --> 00:43:07,234
'I'll just be another minute.'

1066
00:43:07,267 --> 00:43:09,804
'That's alright.
Take your time.'

1067
00:43:12,339 --> 00:43:14,909
Tough one, huh?

1068
00:43:14,942 --> 00:43:18,312
‐ You okay?
‐ Yeah.

1069
00:43:18,345 --> 00:43:21,148
You sure?

1070
00:43:21,181 --> 00:43:22,282
Kept asking
for his daughter.

1071
00:43:24,885 --> 00:43:26,353
Never thought of it
like that, you know?

1072
00:43:29,824 --> 00:43:31,325
Maybe he was asking for me.

1073
00:43:33,327 --> 00:43:35,730
Maybe he wanted to see me
and I never came.

1074
00:43:38,866 --> 00:43:40,901
Your dad was probably
in a coma, Carol.

1075
00:43:40,935 --> 00:43:42,069
I don't know.

1076
00:43:43,971 --> 00:43:45,439
I've been living
my mother's version of it

1077
00:43:45,472 --> 00:43:49,810
for so long, I don't know...
what memories of him are mine.

1078
00:43:49,844 --> 00:43:52,813
‐ What's her version?
‐ Everything was alright.

1079
00:43:52,847 --> 00:43:54,248
That it was an accident.

1080
00:44:00,520 --> 00:44:04,058
He was depressed, Doug.

1081
00:44:04,091 --> 00:44:06,060
Well, maybe it's time
you talked to your mom about it.

1082
00:44:13,033 --> 00:44:15,402
After he was gone,
my mom used to go on and on

1083
00:44:15,435 --> 00:44:18,272
about how you can
never depend on men.

1084
00:44:19,373 --> 00:44:21,575
Now she's head over heels and..

1085
00:44:21,608 --> 00:44:23,010
...I'm the one holding back.

1086
00:44:23,043 --> 00:44:24,879
How messed up is that?

1087
00:44:24,912 --> 00:44:27,514
Keeps me on my toes.

1088
00:44:32,486 --> 00:44:33,954
I say I want time,
but the truth is..

1089
00:44:37,424 --> 00:44:40,394
...I'm scared to death
of losing you.

1090
00:44:40,427 --> 00:44:41,428
Oh, don't be.

1091
00:44:44,064 --> 00:44:46,533
I'm so sorry, Doug.

1092
00:44:46,566 --> 00:44:47,902
Don't be.

1093
00:44:50,170 --> 00:44:52,106
I love you.

1094
00:44:52,139 --> 00:44:53,841
I love you, too.
